#####################################################
#FOR ASSIGN INTERFACES and SOURCES to FIREWALL ZONES#
#####################################################

# INVENTORY_HOST = all/list of inventory hosts separated by ",".
    # If "all" -> the configuration will be applied to all inventory hosts.
    # It is forbidden to include the same interface in several firewall zones.
    # If you want to apply the settings to a group of hosts or to all hosts, then make sure that each host has the interfaces specified in the #INTERFACE_LIST parameter.
    # Configurations like "all" have low priority over host groups (separated by ",") or individual hosts.
###
# FIREWALL_ZONE_NAME_TMPLT = name of the firewall zone template configured in the files "01_conf_custom_firewall_zones_templates" and "01_conf_standard_firewall_zones_templates".
###
# INTERFACE_LIST = list of interfaces, separated by ",".
###
# SOURCE_LIST = list of sources/ipsets, separated by ",".
    # ipset must be preconfigured in file "02_conf_ipsets".
    # Higher priority than setting "INTERFACE_LIST".
###
# RICH_RULES_SET = name of rich rules set for apply to firewall zone. To configure #RICH_RULES_SET edit file "04_conf_zone_rich_rules_sets".
    # Possible values: 
	# some_rich_rule_set_name (for apply some rich rules to firewall zone)
	# empty (for don't apply any rich rules to firewall zone).
###
#INVENTORY_HOST		#FIREWALL_ZONE_NAME_TMPLT		#INTERFACE_LIST			#SOURCE_LIST							#RICH_RULES_SET
#all			public--TMPLT				ens1,ens2,ens3 			10.10.16.0/24,192.168.16.0/24,ipset:ipset_for_all_public	empty (example)
#10.3.2.2		public--TMPLT				eth11,eth12,eth13		10.10.15.0/24,192.168.15.0/24,ipset:ipset_for_public		rich_rules_set_for_public (example)
#10.1.2.3,10.1.2.4	zone1--TMPLT				eth0,eth1,ens01			10.10.11.0/24,192.168.11.0/24,ipset:ipset_for_zone1		rich_rules_set_zone1 (example)
